** General (including keywords & terms)

1. Win + h

2. Alt + F4

3. Win + up arrow

4. Both are a way of converting human written code into binary, so it can executed
   Compiled    -> translate the human written code into a binary code file
   Interpreted -> the computer has a built in interpreter which translates the human written code line by line

5. UEFI         -> Firmware that initialises hardware & launches EFI applications
   Boot Manager -> Part of UEFI that decides which EFI program to start
   Bootloader   -> Loads the OS kernel (GRUB or Windows Boot Manager)

6. API (Application Programming Interface) is a way for different software systems to communicate with each other

7. TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) is a reliable protocol that ensures data is delivered accurately and in order

8. UDP (User Datagram Protocol) is a faster but less reliable protocol that sends data without checking for errors or order

9. DNS (Domain Name System) translates human-readable domain names (like google.com) into IP addresses

10. FTP (File Transfer Protocol) is used to transfer files between a client and a server over a network

11. SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol) is used to send emails between servers

12. To take data in 1 format & convert it into a format that a program can understand


